Simple multiplication
This Question is about multiplying a given number by eight if it is an even number and by nine otherwise.

INPUT 1:

4

OUTPUT 1:

32

INPUT 2:

3

OUTPUT 2:

27
import java.util.*;
public class multiply{
    public static int simpleMultiplication(int n)
    {
        int k=0;
        if(n%2==0)
         k=n*8;
         else
         k=n*9;
    return k;    //write your logic here
    }
    

public static void main(String[] args){
Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
int a=sc.nextInt();
System.out.println(simpleMultiplication(a));
}}
